%% Better-call-behdad — end-to-end audit flow
%% Clean, plain-text labels (no <br/>, no & entities, no emojis) so it imports well.
%% Ready to transliterate to MarkChart once the FLOW_FORMAT spec is available.
flowchart TD
    A[User runs /behdad on a project] --> B[0 Understand and scope]
    B --> C[1 Deterministic scan with real tools]
    C --> D[2 Inspect - 7 specialists run in parallel]
    D --> E[3 Critic gate - verify each finding, drop false positives]
    E --> F[4 Aggregate - dedup, rank by real risk, gate low confidence]
    F --> G[Two reports - Full Diagnostic plus Prioritized Action]
    G --> H{5 You approve the fixes?}
    H -- No --> X[Stop - nothing is changed]
    H -- Yes --> I[6 Remediate - snapshot, apply, verify]
    I --> J{Verification passes?}
    J -- Yes --> K[Fix kept]
    J -- No --> L[Auto-rollback, reported honestly]
    K --> M[7 Learn - remember dismissed findings]
    L --> M
    X --> M
    M --> N[Done]
